[name]
check_clamd

[info]
Tests CLAMD connections with the specified host (or unix socket).

[why]
To make sure the clam antivirus daemon is running and is responding.

[how]
Connects to the clam daemont either via TCP or the local unix socket. The received string is parsed.

[platforms]
Any host running Clamd

